blog.name: angelofberlin2000
blog.title: Like a Rose trampled on the ground
blog.description:
In addition to the pain and the exhaustion, he recalled how waiting on the cross between takes became tedious. To fight the boredom, he listened to music on headphones. One particular song called "Above All" (Like a Rose ...) by Michael W. Smith helped him through his most difficult moments.

"It arrived when I was confused and angry. I didn't think I could go on. The song described how Jesus was rejected and alone. That thought took me to a place — it opened an interior door that held me while on the cross," an emotional Caviezel explained. "The experience of feeling rejected and alone as all those around me laughed while drinking their hot coffees, oblivious to what was occurring. Jesus must have felt like this — forsaken, rejected, alone, and despised. It helped me pray in a very deep way — to pray without words, to pray from the heart. The discomfort, the loneliness, the split shoulder, the raw flesh all forced me into the arms of God because I had nowhere else to go for a performance I knew I was unable to create."
Jim Caviezel, Shamelessly Catholic

summary: 'Bill and Ted 3' Release Date: Filming To Start In March? Potential Christmas Premiere Teased
title: 'Bill and Ted 3' Release Date: Filming To Start In March? Potential Christmas Premiere Teased
body:
HOME

|

GLOBAL

‘Bill and Ted 3’ Release Date: Filming To Start In March? Potential Christmas Premiere Teased 

Rachel Cruz

Feb 08, 2019 06:04 PM

Is Keanu Reeves finally going to work on “Bill and Ted 3” this March with Alex Winter? Rumors suggest that filming may be underway after years of pre-production delays.

A note appearing on Production Weekly’s latest filming schedules indicated that principal photography for “Bill and Ted 3,” officially titled “Bill and Ted Face the Music,” will start on March 5. The cast and crew are also reportedly going to film in locations across Los Angeles, Temple and Phoenix.

Producer Steven Soderbergh also teased in a recent interview with CNET that “Bill and Ted 3” might have Christmas release as a fitting gift to the fans. Fans of the franchise, who followed the 1989 debut and the 1991 sequel, were even more excited when the official Bill & Ted 3 became Twitter-verified last Feb. 8.

However, despite all that’s going on, Orion Pictures apparently denied that the movie will begin filming. What this may mean is that the third installment won’t likely be ready by December.

It is definitely taking “Bill and Ted 3” a while to get off the ground. Development started nearly a decade ago when Reeves revealed that the franchise’s original writers, Chris Matheson and Ed Solomon, were working on a new script.

Six years, and a number of delays later, Winter confirmed that “Bill and Ted 3” has the writers, director Dean Parisot and a production studio, thus work might start by 2017. However, by 2018 and still, with no film to show for, Solomon explained that pre-production has been taking so long because they wanted to get “Bill and Ted” creatively right.

“Bill and Ted” centers on two dim-witted teenage boys who want nothing more than to be famous musicians. A mysterious man, however, lures them into getting on a time machine where they changed and affected the course of history. Apparently, it’s Bill and Ted’s music that holds so much importance in the fate of the world in the future.

The follow-up movie finds Bill and Ted at war with the Grim Reaper. The two go back to the present day to win in the Battle of the Bands.

The third movie will reportedly focus on Bill and Ted as middle-aged men with families and daily routines. They’re still not famous music artists, though, but a new chance to time travel brings another kind of excitement in their lives.

summary: DATING KEANU REEVES WOULD INCLUDE … A/N: Ah, my sweet Keanu. One of the first members of our VIP list and still... no one could...
caption:
DATING KEANU REEVES WOULD INCLUDE …

A/N: Ah, my sweet Keanu. One of the first members of our VIP list and still… no one could ever replace his site. Enjoy it! 

  • Every since the beginning of your dates, both felt the hunch that you were together in other lives. 
  • And all his relatives could tell as well, because no matter how many girls he has been with, no one could beat the unique true love stares he gives you.
  • He’s truly mad in love because every time you talk, even silly jokes, he smiles like a foolish. 
  • And ALWAYS - it doesn’t matter if you are mad at each other- there’s got to be hands caressing as a lovely gesture for your love. Soft kisses on the cheeks, hands caressing your hair or how his hands cup your cheeks and shrinks to kiss your lips.  
  • Supporting each other’s work; never restraining because all he wants is you to be yourself, feel complete, happy with him. 
  • Making breakfast together while dancing at some random music, laughing and kissing each other until you smell food burning.  
  • He constantly shows you off with his friends and his eyes always light out of proud, even the girlfriends of his friends are slightly jealous of how much Keanu loves you. 
  • Jealousy? not so much. He fully trusts you with all his heart, but if your ex’s or some random dude keeps bothering you, he will transform into a beast, threatening them to leave you alone.
  • Opening doors for you - ohh myy-. 
  • He is amazed by your beauty, that’s why you always catch him gazing at you.
  • Every time, he gets flustered, bc it feels like the first time he saw you. 
  • Always checking if you eat, sleep, or rest enough. And if you had a bad day, he would prepare you a warm bath, he massages your head while you tell him about your day. 
  • Once in a while you go out in a fancy restaurant to forget about the monotony of the city, talking about your childhood stories, laughing about something that occur in your work or gossiping about the people you don’t like.  
  • Late night conversations when neither of you can sleep.  
  • A lot of Facetime while he’s off filming or promoting for his newest movie
  • Forehead kisses.  
  • Him bringing you presents every time he’s out of town.
  • ugh, I want this with my future husband. :(

  • Once in a while you go out in a fancy restaurant to forget about the monotony of the city, talking about your childhood stories, laughing about something that occur in your work or gossiping about the people you don’t like.  
  • Late night conversations when neither of you can sleep.  
  • A lot of Facetime while he’s off filming or promoting for his newest movie
  • Forehead kisses.  
  • Him bringing you presents every time he’s out of town.
  • ugh, I want this with my future husband. :(

blog.name: angelofberlin2000
blog.title: Like a Rose trampled on the ground
blog.description:
In addition to the pain and the exhaustion, he recalled how waiting on the cross between takes became tedious. To fight the boredom, he listened to music on headphones. One particular song called "Above All" (Like a Rose ...) by Michael W. Smith helped him through his most difficult moments.

"It arrived when I was confused and angry. I didn't think I could go on. The song described how Jesus was rejected and alone. That thought took me to a place — it opened an interior door that held me while on the cross," an emotional Caviezel explained. "The experience of feeling rejected and alone as all those around me laughed while drinking their hot coffees, oblivious to what was occurring. Jesus must have felt like this — forsaken, rejected, alone, and despised. It helped me pray in a very deep way — to pray without words, to pray from the heart. The discomfort, the loneliness, the split shoulder, the raw flesh all forced me into the arms of God because I had nowhere else to go for a performance I knew I was unable to create."
Jim Caviezel, Shamelessly Catholic
